From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keyur Maru <kd2maru@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 05:10:06 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] rmnetctl: always build the legacy rmnet ioctl API

librmnetctl gates the old ioctl-based rmnet API behind the rmnetctl.old_rmnet_data
soong config variable. That select was not being applied on this target even
though the device sets it (sdm632-common BoardConfigCommon.mk), so librmnetctl.so
shipped only the newer rtrmnet_* netlink API and the A10-era netmgrd / adpl vendor
blobs failed to resolve rmnetctl_init and
rmnet_set_link_ingress_data_format_tailspace at dlopen time, taking down data.

The USE_OLD_RMNET_DATA block is purely additive (the rtrmnet_* entry points stay),
so define it unconditionally instead of relying on the select. This board runs a
4.9 kernel with the old rmnet_data driver, so the legacy API is the one that
matches the kernel anyway.
---
 rmnetctl/Android.bp | 12 ++++++++----
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/rmnetctl/Android.bp b/rmnetctl/Android.bp
index cc0fef5..d1a0760 100644
--- a/rmnetctl/Android.bp
+++ b/rmnetctl/Android.bp
@@ -9,10 +9,14 @@ cc_defaults {
     cflags: [
         "-Wall",
         "-Werror",
-    ] + select(soong_config_variable("rmnetctl", "old_rmnet_data"), {
-        "true": ["-DUSE_OLD_RMNET_DATA"],
-        default: [],
-    }),
+        // channel A17: force the OLD rmnet ioctl API on unconditionally. The soong_config
+        // select (rmnetctl.old_rmnet_data, set in device BoardConfigCommon.mk:282) was NOT
+        // being applied, so librmnetctl.so shipped only the new rtrmnet_* netlink API and the
+        // A10 netmgrd/adpl vendor blobs failed dlopen at runtime on rmnetctl_init /
+        // rmnet_set_link_ingress_data_format_tailspace. The USE_OLD_RMNET_DATA block is
+        // ADDITIVE (keeps rtrmnet_*), so hardcoding it is safe on this 4.9-kernel board.
+        "-DUSE_OLD_RMNET_DATA",
+    ],
     header_libs: ["librmnetctl_headers"],
     vendor: true,
 }
